Cell.Text: Malkoran is vanquished. Skyrim's dead shall remain at rest. This is as it should be. This is because of you. | A new day is dawning. And you shall be it's herald. | Take the mighty Dawnbreaker and with it purge corruption from the dark corners of the world. Wield it in my name, that my influence may grow.
[S] G|May the light of certitude guide your efforts.

Node.Caption: DA09MeridiaDawnbreakerYes: I'll wield this mighty blade in your name.

Cell.Text: [S] G|It matters not. The plant cares nothing for the rays that bring it the warmth of the sun. As you carry Dawnbreaker, so will my light touch the world.

Node.Caption: DA09MeridiaDawnbreakerNo: I'll keep the sword, but find someone else to spread your religion.

Cell.Text: The Necromancer Malkoran defiles my shrine with vile corruptions, trapping lost souls left in the wake of this war to do his bidding. | Worse still, he uses the power stored within my own token to fuel his foul deeds. | I have brought you here, mortal, to be my champion. You will enter my temple, retrieve my artifact, and destroy the defiler.
G|Guide my light through the temple to open the inner sanctum and destroy the defiler.

Cell.Text: But a single candle can banish the darkness of the entire Void. If not you, than someone else. | My beacon is sure to attract a worthy soul. | But if you are wise, you will heed my bidding.

Node.Caption: DA09MeridiaQuestWhy: It doesn't really sound like I have a choice in the matter.

Cell.Text: Of course you will. I have commanded it!

Node.Caption: DA09MeridiaQuestYes: I'll do it.

Cell.Text: [S] G|Go now, the artifact must be reclaimed and Malkoran destroyed.

Mortals call it Dawnbreaker, for it was forged in a holy light that breaks upon my foes, burning away corruption and false life. | You will enter my shrine, destroy Malkoran, and retrieve this mighty blade.

Node.Caption: DA09MeridiaArtifact: Tell me more about this artifact.
